                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   We had a short amount of time before catching a flight and didn't have time to overthink options. We searched nearby places for a breakfast burrito and chose Robles Mexican Grill as it was nearby and had good ratings.
                   <br/>
                   A sign greeted us listing any breakfast burrito with a drink for $8.99 !
                   <br/>
                   It was early (8 am) the restaurant was empty and were seated with a basket of chips and some delicious fresh salsa. We went ahead and ordered two specials since we both wanted drinks. The hostess / waitress asked if we wanted "everything " in our burritos - potatoes/beans/eggs/ cheese/ /meat - which we accepted- might as well try it is to judge it fairly.
                   <br/>
                   In less than 10 mins the waitress brought 2 of the largest burritos we ever recall  seeing! The burritos were absolutely delicious: the tortilla wraps were toasted, and the filling was lightly seasoned.
                   <br/>
                   We normally do not care for potatoes in a breakfast burrito but these somehow just worked. The two of us shared a burrito then had a few bites of the other and took it to go.
                   <br/>
                   Very happy with this quick find- service and food both 5 stars!
                  </span>
                 </p>

                   <span alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="icon--16-camera-v2 css-6a0jil" role="img">
                    <svg class="icon_svg" height="16" width="16">
                     <path d="M3.06 14.76a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084-2.083V5.344A2.091 2.091 0 0 1 3.06 3.25h1.393l.496-1.487a.75.75 0 0 1 .711-.513h4.334a.75.75 0 0 1 .711.513l.496 1.487h1.74a2.086 2.086 0 0 1 2.083 2.083v7.334a2.086 2.086 0 0 1-2.084 2.083l-9.88.01Zm0-10.01a.59.59 0 0 0-.584.594v7.333a.584.584 0 0 0 .584.584l9.88-.011a.584.584 0 0 0 .584-.583V5.333a.584.584 0 0 0-.584-.583h-2.28a.75.75 0 0 1-.711-.513L9.453 2.75H6.201l-.496 1.487a.75.75 0 0 1-.711.513H3.06Z">
                     </path>
                     <path d="M8 12.556a3.75 3.75 0 1 1 0-7.501 3.75 3.75 0 0 1 0 7.5Zm0-6a2.25 2.25 0 1 0 0 4.5 2.25 2.25 0 0 0 0-4.5Z">
                     </path>
                    </svg>
                   </span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="css-1oibaro" data-font-weight="semibold">
                   <a class="css-19v1rkv" href="/biz_photos/robles-mexican-grill-and-taqueria-fresno?userid=5XkCh94jeQUFsPOQm2n2JA">
                    2 photos
                   </a>
                  </span>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   This place is bomb! I found this place through yelp one day when I was looking for more of a authentic taste for Mexican food. It's a small little mom-n-pop kind of vibe. I was actually shocked that this place wasn't slammed wall-to-wall with people because the food is really really good. I might be a gringo but I know Mexican food!
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The inside is super clean. The service is quick and the mesera was super nice.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I tried the Jamaica. It was really good and clean. I ordered the quesa birria tacos--those were fire. The meat wasn't chewy and tasted excellent. The tortillas were made well and weren't easily soggy or mushy. They tasted great with the consume (bomb as well) and the salsa.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I also ordered menudo. Now I'm super picky when it comes to menudo. I like the tripe to be soft not chewy. This one was super soft and the pieces weren't all huge. They were a good size. The broth was delicious and had good flavor, you didn't have to add salt to it or lemon--only if you wanted additional flavoring.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Overall, the place is one of my new top favorites. Go try it out.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                   <span class="css-chan6m">
                    Jul 11, 2023
                   </span>

                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Found this place during COVID, ordered religiously because of how delicious it was. Being Mexican ourselves, we tend to be very picky and critical of Mexican restaurants and it's hard to find one that tastes like it was cooked in our own kitchen. This place is hands down one of the best, if not the best Mexican restaurant in Fresno! There are some menu items that are not incredibly delicious, but the items that are make up for everything else (IMO).
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Their breakfast burritos, California burritos, quesabirria are our favorites. And I can't forget their albóndigas soup, easily the best I've had in the Central Valley.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Definitely recommend this place and we'll continue to order food from here for years to come!
                  </span>
                 </p>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   We came here on a weeknight and there were about 3 other tables. Looks like there are about 8 tables total inside. It is a normal sit down restaurant with waiter service and our waiter was very sweet and attentive.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The food itself is priced very reasonably. I paid about $12 for a combination plate with chicken enchiladas and a Birria taco, and the chips and salsa were complimentary. My friend paid $18 for 4 tacos carne asada and a large horchata.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Everything I had was really good but some of it was a little bland. Like the enchiladas sauce could have had more of a pop to it, as well as the Birria taco, which was sort of missing a kick to it. But overall the food was good and the restaurant is clean and priced well. I would definitely come back and try the other menu items.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Fresno has a lot of really good Mexican restaurants. You should add this to your go-to list: Robles Mexican Grill and Taqueria. It's on the corner of Fresno and McKenzie. my queso birria tacos, and the consommé that you dip them into, we're amazing! Nephew devoured three different tacos, and espisa got the Molcajete (check out the picture below) which had beef, chorizo, chicken, shrimp, Napolis, cheese, jalapeños, green onions, all of this amazing sauce. Did I mention the homemade corn tortillas  We'll  be back!
                  </span>
                 </p>

                  <div class="arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg arrange-unit-fill__09f24__CUubG css-1qn0b6x">
                   <span class="css-chan6m">
                    Feb 20, 2023
                   </span>

                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Although there was nothing technically wrong with the food, it just wasn't that memorable. The salsa and the chips were delicious and I was surprised they were so fresh being that I was the first person in the restaurant this morning. I do like that it is very roomy that you don't feel like you're sitting in somebody's lap. The jabbering TV set was turned to mute at my request. Mindless background stimulation that is entirely unnecessary... constantly annoys me.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I ordered an à la cart carne Asada taco, a chicken enchilada with red sauce and a muchacha breakfast burrito. As usual I requested extra onion... I also asked for extra cheese on the burrito, and she assured me that I would have both. My beloved simple water is always riding shotgun! Even tap would be fine...
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   What immediately struck me about the chicken enchilada was the low grade quality of the cheese on top. It tasted pre-shredded and very plastic-like immediately bringing the potential of the dish down.  I don't know why any place would purchase such poor quality of cheese. It essentially ruins the meal it is so noticeable you never want to return... the red sauce was delicious and the enchilada was otherwise competent. The purely shredded chicken interior was not that great and would've benefited from the onions I requested, but did not receive....
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The Carne Asada taco was OK, the meat was good but not that flavorful. And it seemed like the right portion.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The burrito was very basic. I picked most of the potatoes out of it and cut off excess tortilla that had nothing in it. ..
                   <br/>
                   The filling was just too finely mixed with the eggs and the rest of it. Nothing was distinct or flavorful. It did not have any snap/texture from the additional onions requested, but we're not included. .. it was a good size but not that tasty. It also did not have cheese on it, which would turn out to be a blessing. Although I ordered extra and believe I paid for it...
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The service was wonderful, and the waitress checked on me a couple times and was pleasant. I thought the three items that I ordered would provide a good representation of the overall quality of the menu. And although I wouldn't put up a fuss to eat here again, I wouldn't exactly look forward to it either. Perhaps there's a couple really fantastic items which I completely missed?
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   In the end, they didn't not add the additional onions I requested or the extra cheese on the burrito (which turned out to be a God send!). but don't you hate it when somebody tells you they will for sure do something and they don't? That's a quality that I immediately note. It definitely contributes to the decision to never return again... I don't like passive aggressiveness in anybody, much less a restaurant..
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The fact that my server knew it was my first time there makes my decision even more pronounced. Not gonna happen twice...

                   One new place down and 1000 more to go!
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   -G

                     <path d="M8 12.556a3.75 3.75 0 1 1 0-7.501 3.75 3.75 0 0 1 0 7.5Zm0-6a2.25 2.25 0 1 0 0 4.5 2.25 2.25 0 0 0 0-4.5Z">
                     </path>
                    </svg>
                   </span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="css-1oibaro" data-font-weight="semibold">
                   <a class="css-19v1rkv" href="/biz_photos/robles-mexican-grill-and-taqueria-fresno?userid=zs7QdZmHL0s5eU62GnIMgQ">
                    7 photos
                   </a>
                  </span>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   The food was amazing! Probably one of the better tacos I've had in Fresno. The meat was super flavorful. They provided a variety of sauces for the food as well. I'm a saucy girl. I love sauce. But the taco didn't need sauce. That's how you know a taco is good when all you need is lemon. (5/5)
                   <br/>
                   The sopes is okay, it was my first time having it. I'm not a big fan of the shell. I know that's probably how it's supposed to be but with all the toppings and everything already on it made the sopes soggy. But the toppings were nice. (3/5)
                   <br/>
                   The mojarra Frita was good, super crispy. I think it could've used some salt, I don't think it was seasoned. Butttt they do provide salt on the table and like I mentioned before they give a lot of sauces so they made up the flavor. The rice they provided was good. Standard rice. The beans were a tad bit too runny for me personally. But the rice and beans were both seasoned well. (3.5/5)
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Overall the food was good. The tacos were the best. I also saw everyone getting the 7 seas soup. I will definitely be getting that. I'm assuming that's what they're known for. But I will definitely be coming back especially for those tacos.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   This was my third time here and yes I would totally recommend this place. The staff is friendly and fast, as soon as you walk in, you are greeted and asked to take a seat,  they serve chips and salsa at no extra charge. The place is clean and well kept, music playing at all time, I like that its  not too loud and overwhelming, just right! The food is always hot and is served with home made tortillas (corn or flour). Honestly I could come here just for the rice and beans lol and still  be a happy camper, the portions are very generous.
                  </span>

had a short amount of time before catching a flight and didn&#x27;t have time to overthink options. We searched nearby places for a breakfast burrito and chose Robles Mexican Grill as it was nearby and had good ratings. \nA sign greeted us listing any breakfast burrito with a drink for $8.99 !\nIt was early (8 am) the restaurant was empty and were seated with a basket of chips and some delicious fresh salsa. We went ahead and ordered two specials since we both wanted drinks. The hostess &#x2F; waitress asked if we wanted \&quot;everything \&quot; in our burritos - potatoes&#x2F;beans&#x2F;eggs&#x2F; cheese&#x2F; &#x2F;meat - which we accepted- might as well try it is to judge it fairly. \nIn less than 10 mins the waitress brought 2 of the largest burritos we ever recall  seeing! there was nothing technically wrong with the food, it just wasn&#x27;t that memorable. The salsa and the chips were delicious and I was surprised they were so fresh being that I was the first person in the restaurant this morning. I do like that it is very roomy that you don&#x27;t feel like you&#x27;re sitting in somebody&#x27;s lap. The jabbering TV set was turned to mute at my request. Mindless background stimulation that is entirely unnecessary... constantly annoys me.\n\nI ordered an à la cart carne Asada taco, a chicken enchilada with red sauce and a muchacha breakfast burrito. As usual I requested extra onion... I also asked for extra cheese on the burrito, and she assured me that I would have both. My beloved simple water is always riding shotgun! Even tap would be fine...\n\nWhat immediately struck me about the chicken enchilada was the low grade quality of the cheese on top. It tasted pre-shredded and very plastic-like immediately bringing the potential of the dish down.  I don&#x27;t know why any place would purchase such poor quality of cheese. It essentially ruins the meal it is so noticeable you never want to return... the red sauce was delicious and the enchilada was otherwise competent. The purely shredded chicken interior was not that great and would&#x27;ve benefited from the onions I requested, but did not receive....\n\nThe Carne Asada taco was OK, the meat was good but not that flavorful. And it seemed like the right portion. \n\nThe burrito was very basic. I picked most of the potatoes out of it and cut off excess tortilla that had nothing in it. ..\nThe filling was just too finely mixed with the eggs and the rest of it. Nothing was distinct or flavorful. It did not have any snap&#x2F;texture from the additional onions requested, but we&#x27;re not included. .. it was a good size but not that tasty. It also did not have cheese on it, which would turn out to be a blessing. Although I ordered extra and believe I paid for it...\n\nThe service was wonderful, and the waitress checked on me a couple times and was pleasant. I thought the three items that I ordered would provide a good representation of the overall quality of the menu. And although I wouldn&#x27;t put up a fuss to eat here again, I wouldn&#x27;t exactly look forward to it either. Perhaps there&#x27;s a couple really fantastic items which I completely missed?\n\nIn the end, they didn&#x27;t not add the additional onions I requested or the extra cheese on the burrito (which turned out to be a God send!). but don&#x27;t you hate it when somebody tells you they will for sure do something and they don&#x27;t? That&#x27;s a quality that I immediately note. It definitely contributes to the decision to never return again... I don&#x27;t like passive aggressiveness in anybody, much less a restaurant..\n\nThe fact that my server knew it was my first time there makes my decision even more pronounced. Not gonna happen twice...\n\nOne new place down and 1000 more to
